Steps to Solve:

1. Find a Prototype Pollution Source

Inject an arbitrary property into Object.prototype using the query string:
/?__proto__[foo]=bar

Open DevTools → Console and execute:
Object.prototype

Verify that the injected foo property has been added to Object.prototype.

2. Identify the Gadget

Open DevTools → Sources and inspect the JavaScript files.

In searchLogger.js, notice that config.transport_url is used to dynamically set the src attribute of a <script> element.

Also observe that the transport_url property is not defined in the config object, making it possible to inherit the value from Object.prototype.

3. Confirm the Gadget

Inject a transport_url property into Object.prototype:
/?__proto__[transport_url]=foo

Open DevTools → Elements and verify that the page creates:
<script src="foo"></script>

This confirms that the gadget is controllable through prototype pollution.

4. Trigger DOM XSS

Replace the payload with a data: URL:
/?__proto__[transport_url]=data:,alert(1);

The application creates the following script element:
<script src="data:,alert(1);"></script>

The browser executes:
alert(1)

The lab is now solved.

